8:
Is that really all you're capable of?
How pathetic.
11:
Tsk... And here I was, thinking I'd get
some amusement out of this. How
disappointing.
17:
You dare steal the techniques I
honed and made my own?
21:
You've got guts—ones that I'll rip out
of you.
25: So this is the strength of a monster.
32:
Just thinking about that moment
makes me sick... How could I allow
myself to lose like that?
34: There's only one way to find out...
40:
Now, then. Fetch me my dinner—and
that mad dog, while you're at it.
43: Why exactly are you here, again?
47:
Don't tell me you've forgotten your
end of the bargain.
50:
You seriously expect me to make
you dinner after you suddenly
turned on us?
53:
What? I didn't kill anyone. The
operative word there being "I."
57:
I stayed perfectly true to our
contract. Stop grumbling and do as
you promised.
61:
Fine. I'll make you dinner. But I won't
tell you where Helga is.
64:
How about a deal: bring her to me
and I'll give you a pass on one
week's worth of dinner.
68:
I'm not biting. This sounds very
much like a you problem.
71:
Why hello there, you two. Up to no
good, I take it?
75: There she is—the mad dog herself.
80:
Out of my way. Unless you have a
death wish.
88:
Nothing to fret about, boy. I won't kill
her.
93:
I see. Your fists hunger for more.
Were they not sated before?
96:
Our previous battle, you mean? You
can't expect me to admit defeat
after that ludicrous display.
100:
You've found it, haven't you? The
way to become the most powerful
warrior alive?
104:
Hmm... Let's just put it this way: it's
not a path that I can see you
walking, Little Lady.
107:
You know nothing about me.
Enough—time to let our fists do the
talking.
112: Goodness. Is she always like this?
116:
Hard to say. She's normally a bit
more... composed. She looks hungry
for a fight. More than usual.
119:
There's nothing more useless than a
warrior without an appetite for war.
121:
Come now. Be a good dog and
show me what tricks you've learned.
123:
Or are you nothing more than an
inept mongrel?
127:
Very well—you've piqued my
interest. I'll humor you with a fight.
133:
W-wait a second! Helga, are you
sure about this?!
136:
Don't fret, Alk. This is familiar territory
for me—I call the battlefield my
home, after all.
141:
Haha! Do you see, boy? It's in her
very nature.
144:
I'm glad to see you've grown more
receptive.
148:
Before we continue, I must append a
few conditions.
155:
Let's make a deal. Your reputation
says you're the type who takes
contracts very seriously.
158:
So how about this... For the duration
of one month, you'll do whatever Alk
tells you.
167:
You understand her better than
most, don't you? This will be a
perfect opportunity to... put a leash
on her.
171:
A leash, huh? In that case... Shuilong,
no more picking fights. Oh, and you'll
be helping me with the dishes and
laundry. We've also got some
shopping to do today—
175:
Now hold on a minute. I'm not sure I
like the tone you're taking with me,
boy.
178:
If it really bothers you, I can try to
work on that. Why don't we add that
to the contract too?
179:
Oh, and if we're being picky about
word choice... I think I'd like you to try
to sound nicer—and stop calling me
"boy" all the time.
181: I have a name, you know. It's Alk.
184:
Fine. Just shut your mouth
already—all this talk is irritating me.
188:
...Now that I think about it, forget that
last part. It's way too unrealistic.
192:
You make no sense to me
whatsoever.
197:
Do make sure to listen to everything
Alk tells you. If you don't carry out
your end of the bargain, I won't be
fighting you.
201:
Hmph... No need to harp on about
it—I've already agreed.
204:
But remember, this agreement goes
both ways... And I don't take kindly to
breaches of contract.
207:
I'm well aware. Do Alk's bidding, and
I'll take you in a fight. As promised.
209:
Though I don't know if our battle will
be everything you're building it up to
be.
213: That settles it, then. Let's go.
220:
That's a debt you'll have to pay later.
We've got more important things to
do now.
222:
I figure with no rest or sleep, I should
be able to knock out one month's
work in about three days.
230:
Quit your whining. We have work to
do.
